## Design decisions (confirmed with user)

- **Dependency management:** stdlib `venv` + `requirements.txt` (mirrors the Ruby side's
  minimal-Gemfile philosophy ŌĆö no Poetry/uv). `requirements.txt` needs `python-dotenv`
  (equivalent of the `dotenv` gem) and `PyYAML` (stdlib has no YAML parser, and the
  shared `settings.yaml` format is fixed since Ruby also reads it ŌĆö this is the one new
  dependency the Ruby version didn't need).
- **Code style:** literal mirror of the Ruby OO design ŌĆö keep `Config`, `Tasks.Base`,
  `Tasks.Player` as classes with classmethods/staticmethods, `Base` as an ABC-like
  class raising `NotImplementedError` for `task_name`. Do not redesign into plain
  functions/dataclasses, so the two trees stay comparable step-by-step.
- **Tests:** none for this step, matching Ruby parity. Only the runnable
  `examples/example.py` smoke test. Revisit if/when the Ruby side adds `rspec`.

